						               													<description>Magmell (&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#158;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#176;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#171;) is an anime-themed expandable card game that features competitive one-versus-one battles, familiar card battle mechanics, and gorgeous anime art.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Magmell, players build a deck from a pool of 180 cards and then square off against one another in alternating-turn format. There are four types of cards that players must get acquainted with in Magmell: Unit Cards, Magic Cards, Crystal Cards, and Other Cards. Creating a deck that has a balance of all four types is critical to success.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a player's turn, they can draw cards, play resource Crystals, summon units, activate spells, and engage in battle. During combat, the attacked player has the ability to choose who their defenders are, giving them some control over how each combat round plays out. Opponents alternate back and forth, taking turns and engaging in the aforementioned turn options until one of their life pools reaches 0.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
